fields.description:
Space import has a concept of 'renaming' a space key based on a new key defined in the {{exportDescriptor.properties}}. This renaming happens in the {{SpaceImportPreProcessor}}, and overrides the space key in the {{entities.xml}} file. The same should be happening for Bandana records (that have their context set as the space key of the associated space) but it isn't because of a conditional in {{AbstractBandanaImportPreProcessor}}, which is stricter than the one in {{SpaceImportPreProcessor}}. 

This means the {{updateProperty}} method runs for one, but not the other. So, the Bandana context is saved with a different space key. If the space import fails for another reason, or that space is ever deleted, the Bandana record won't get cleaned up because {{deleteSpace}} doesn't delete it. If the import is then retried, the following error is hit, and the import consistently fails.

{{Caused by: org.postgresql.util.PSQLException: ERROR: duplicate key value violates unique constraint "bandana_unique_key"}}

h3. Summary
CSS code not working on pages.

h3. Steps to Reproduce
Add the following lines in the CSS Stylesheet macro on a page.
{code}
.page-metadata {display:none;}
#comments-section { display:none; }
#likes-and-labels-container { display:none; }
#main-header { display:none; }
#create-page-button { display:none; }
#footer { display:none; }
#quick-create-page-button { display:none; }
{code}

h3. Expected Results
The icons for editing, managing watchers, etc. should not be displayed on the top right of the page.

h3. Actual Results
The CSS code has no effect on the page.

h3. Summary
Using REST API endpoints like this:
https://INSTANCENAME.atlassian.net/wiki/rest/api/content/1234567?expand=body.styled_view
Returns LESS code or other preprocessed CSS code instead of raw CSS.

Furthermore HTML ID's and Classes are not properly Wrapped into the DOM tree.

h3. Environment
Confluence Cloud REST API

h3. Steps to Reproduce
# Log into instance and perform a GET with a URL like this: https://INSTANCENAME.atlassian.net/wiki/rest/api/content/1234567?expand=body.styled_view (be sure to replace the 1234567 with an actual content ID.)
# Observe the returned body.

h3. Expected Results
Body will be returned with working CSS code.

h3. Actual Results
CSS portion of the code looks like this:
{code}
/* wiki-content.css */

/**
* AUI Overrides
* see /includes/css/aui-overrides.css
*/
.rounded-corners (@radius: 5px) {
-moz-border-radius: @radius;
-webkit-border-radius: @radius;
border-radius: @radius;
}

.wiki-content {
.header, .footer, .cell {
{code}
 
This contains nested CSS classes which are not a"vanilla" CSS feature.

Furthermore, you will see code like this:
{code}
.view .wiki-content .cell:first-child,
.content-preview .wiki-content .cell:first-child {
padding: 0;
}
{code}

In the above example, the ".view" class was not in the HTML that was returned with the "body.styled_view" however this HTML class *was* returned in the plain "body.view" expand mode.

h3. Notes
N/A

h3.Workaround
Current workaround is to process the LESS code in your custom application, or to create your own CSS to style the "body.view" return data.

h3.Summary
* Style Macro change the layout of the text box comment.

.wiki-content h4\{
 color:#FFFFFF;
 background-color:#3ea650;
 box-shadow: 3px 3px 3px #333333; 
 margin-right: 3px;
 padding-left: 20px;
 padding-right: 5px;
 font-family: Verdana, Arial, sans-serif;
 font-size:12pt;
 margin-bottom:5px;
}

h3.Steps to reproduce
# Create the page called "style" and insert the style macro to customize the h4 heading with the above lines.
# Create another page called "custom" and include the "style" page on the custom page

h3.Expected Result
* Not changing the layout of the page heading on the comment text box.

h3.Actual Result
* The layout of the page heading on the comment text box is changed.

h3.Workaround
# On the "custom" page insert another style macro for the h4 heading.
